<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747273>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 10. (a–h) Hapalotremus major, male holotype (MCZ 142). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Eyes, dorsal view. (e) Labium and maxillae. (f) Tibial apophysis, ventral view. (g) Leg I, lateral view. (h) Tarsus IV, ventral view. Arrow indicates the spiniform setae on coxa. Scale bars: a–c: 5 mm; d–h: 1 mm. Photos: Rick West." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747273/files/figure.png" .

