<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747275>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 11. (a–d) Hapalotremus major, male holotype (MCZ 142). (a, b) Male right palpal bulb. (a) Retrolateral view. (b) Prolateral view. (c. d) Palpal tibia. (c) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (d) Palpal tibia, ventral view. Arrows indicate the rounded process. A, apical keel; DA, digitiform apophysis; PI, prolateral inferior keel; PS, prolateral superior keel. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Rick West." ;
